### GET ALL USERS
### Retrieves a list of all registered users
### Response: Array of user objects (JSON)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/

###

### GET USER BY ID
### Retrieves a single user by their unique identifier
### @param id - User ID (path parameter)
### Response: Single user object (JSON)
### Example: Get user with ID 1
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/1

###

### CREATE NEW USER
### Adds a new user to the database
### Method: POST
### Request Body: JSON object with user fields
### Required fields: firstName, lastName, email
###
### @param firstName - User's first name (string)
### @param lastName - User's last name (string)
### @param email - User's email address (must be unique)
###
### Response: Created user object with generated ID
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/
# POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/clientes/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Matias",
  "lastName": "Matias",
  "email": "mati@example.com"
}

###

### UPDATE USER (PARTIAL - PUT)
### Updates specific fields of an existing user
### Method: PUT
### @param id - User ID to update (path parameter: /users/4)
### Request Body: JSON object with fields to update
### 
### Note: PUT typically replaces entire resource,
### but this implementation allows partial updates
###
### Response: Updated user object
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/4
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lastName": "Martinez"
}

###

### DELETE USER
### Removes a user from the database
### Method: DELETE
### @param id - User ID to delete (path parameter: /users/4)
###
### Response: Confirmation message or deleted user data
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/4

###

### ============================================
### POST ENDPOINTS
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000/api/v1/posts/
### ============================================

### GET ALL POSTS
### Retrieves a list of all posts from all users
### Response: Array of post objects (JSON)
### Each post includes: id, authorId, text, timestamps
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/posts/

###

### CREATE NEW POST
### Adds a new post to the database
### Method: POST
### Request Body: JSON object with post fields
### Required fields: authorId, text
###
### @param authorId - ID of the user creating the post (integer, must exist)
### @param text - Content of the post (string)
###
### Response: Created post object with generated ID and timestamps
###
### Example: User with ID 5 creates a post
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/posts/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorId": 1,
  "title": "Mi Primer post Mati Matias dejate de joder"
}

###

POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com",
  "password": "1234"
}

### ============================================
### USAGE NOTES:
### ============================================
### 1. Make sure backend server is running on port 3000
### 2. Install REST Client extension in VS Code to use .http files
### 3. Click "Send Request" above each endpoint to execute
### 4. Sequential IDs: /users/1, /users/2, etc. (auto-incremented)
### 5. Foreign key constraint: posts.authorId must reference existing users.id
###
### EXPECTED RESPONSE CODES:
### - 200 OK: Successful GET, PUT, DELETE
### - 201 Created: Successful POST
### - 400 Bad Request: Invalid request body
### - 404 Not Found: User or resource doesn't exist
### - 500 Internal Server Error: Server-side issue
### ============================================